entries.title: Ukraine: Boris Johnson says Putin threatened him with missile strike
entries.description: Boris Johnson says he had an "extraordinary" call with President Putin before the Ukraine invasion.

entries.title: Super Bowl 57: Philadelphia Eagles beat San Francisco 49ers 31-7 to book spot in Arizona
entries.description: The Philadelphia Eagles deny Brock Purdy a fairytale Super Bowl appearance after beating the San Francisco 49ers 31-7 in the Conference Championships.

entries.title: Erdogan says Turkey may block Sweden's Nato membership bid
entries.description: The president said he would not support Sweden's bid until it extradited dozens of "terrorists".

entries.title: Tyre Nichols' lawyer urges lawmakers to pass urgent police reforms
entries.description: Ben Crump urged lawmakers to pass the George Floyd Justice in Policing Act in Nichols' memory.

entries.title: Six Nations: England v Scotland - Henry Slade & Courtney Lawes ruled out
entries.description: Centre Henry Slade and forward Courtney Lawes are ruled out of England's opening Six Nations game against Scotland on Saturday.

entries.title: FA Cup: Wrexham 3-3 Sheffield United - highlights
entries.description: Watch highlights as John Egan's stoppage-time goal rescues a draw for Championship Sheffield United against non-league Wrexham in a frenetic FA Cup fourth-round tie.

entries.title: FA Cup: Wrexham 3-3 Sheffield United - Egan's late strike denies Wrexham victory
entries.description: John Egan's stoppage time goal rescues Sheffield United against non-league Wrexham in a frenetic FA Cup fourth-round tie.

entries.title: FA Cup: Paul Mullin puts Wrexham back in lead against Sheffield United
entries.description: Wrexham forward Paul Mullin puts his side back in front against 10-man Sheffield United in their FA Cup fourth round tie at the Racecourse ground.

entries.title: Dundee United 0-2 Celtic: Visitors break down hosts' resistance to restore nine-point lead
entries.description: Celtic restore their nine-point lead at the top of the Scottish Premiership as they grind down Dundee United's stubborn resistance after the break.

entries.title: 'We wanted a fresh start in 2023 - but we've been worse'
entries.description: Liverpool hoped a new year would bring a change in form - but their FA Cup exit at Brighton is another low in a largely miserable season.

entries.title: FA Cup: Oliver McBurnie heads Sheffield United into early lead at Wrexham
entries.description: Sheffield United forward heads his side into the lead in the second minute of their FA Cup fourth round tie against Wrexham at the Racecourse Ground.

entries.title: German chancellor says he won't send fighter jets to Ukraine
entries.description: The request for the jets comes just days after Germany committed to supplying Leopard 2 tanks.

entries.title: Scottish Prison Service to carry out 'urgent review' of trans inmates
entries.description: The Scottish Prison Service says it will pause the movement of all trans prisoners until the review ends.

entries.title: Ryanair and EasyJet ready to snap up Flybe staff
entries.description: Airlines are inviting employees of the collapsed airline to fill vacancies for cabin crew and other roles.

entries.title: England in South Africa: Touring bowlers struggle as Temba Bavuma hits ton as hosts win ODI series
entries.description: England failed to defend 342 as Temba Bavuma's century in the second ODI helped South Africa clinch a 2-0 series victory.

entries.title: FA Cup: Josh Laurent reclaims Stoke's lead with 'magnificent goal'
entries.description: Watch as Josh Laurent scores "magnificent" goal to reclaim Stoke's lead against Stevenage in the FA Cup.

entries.title: Anthony Gordon: Newcastle sign Everton forward in £45m deal
entries.description: Newcastle United complete the signing of Everton forward Anthony Gordon in a deal that could be worth up to £45m.

entries.title: Brighton & Hove Albion 2-1 Liverpool: Kaoru Mitoma injury-time goal sends FA Cup holders out
entries.description: Kaoru Mitoma scores in stoppage time as Brighton knock holders Liverpool out of the FA Cup with victory at the Amex.

entries.title: Novak Djokovic says 10th Australian Open is his 'biggest victory'
entries.description: Novak Djokovic says winning a 10th Australian Open to equal Rafael Nadal's record 22 Grand Slam men's titles is "the biggest victory" of his life.

entries.title: FA Cup: Kaoru Mitoma scores a sensational late winning goal against Liverpool
entries.description: Watch as Brighton forward Kaoru Mitoma scores a brilliant 92nd-minute goal to send his side through to the FA Cup fifth round at the expense of holders Liverpool.

entries.title: U19 Women's World Cup: Inspired India thrash England in final
entries.description: An inspired India win the first Women's Under-19 World Cup by thrashing England in a one-sided final in South Africa.

entries.title: Dubai Desert Classic: Rory McIlroy leads by three, Patrick Reed four back
entries.description: Rory McIlroy cards a seven-under-par 65 to take a three-shot lead in the rain-delayed Dubai Desert Classic at Emirates.

entries.title: FA Cup: Jacob Brown fires Stoke into the lead against Stevenage
entries.description: Watch as Stoke forward Jacob Brown scores early on to give his side the early lead against Stevenage in the FA Cup.

entries.title: Iran 'foils drone attack' on military facility in Isfahan

entries.title: 'Relief and delight' over bereavement benefit change
entries.description: Parents who are not married can now claim bereavement support payments if they lose a partner.

entries.title: Australian Open 2023: Novak Djokovic beats Stefanos Tsitsipas in Melbourne final
entries.description: The best of the action of Novak Djokovic winning his 10th Australian Open and a record-equalling 22nd Grand Slam men's title.

entries.title: Bridlington: Rescuers search for entangled seal pup spotted by drone
entries.description: As the search for the seal pup continues, rescuers came across another pup with an eye infection.

entries.title: Dame Esther Rantzen reveals lung cancer diagnosis

entries.title: Hexham stabbings: Boy, 16, charged with murdering teenage girl

entries.title: Chris Mason: Zahawi sacking raises questions over Sunak's judgement

entries.title: Australian Open 2023: Novak Djokovic beats Stefanos Tsitsipas in Melbourne final
entries.description: Novak Djokovic wins a record-extending 10th Australian Open and a record-equalling 22nd Grand Slam men's title by seeing off Stefanos Tsitsipas.

entries.title: Man stabbed at Harrods amid reports of a fight
entries.description: Police are appealing for anyone with information about the stabbing to contact them.

entries.title: More than 50 die in two Pakistan accidents

entries.title: Malo Gusto: Chelsea sign teenage right-back from Lyon in £31m deal

entries.title: Nadhim Zahawi committed a serious breach of ministerial code, says Sunak
entries.description: Pressure was mounting on Nadhim Zahawi after it emerged he paid a tax penalty while chancellor.

entries.title: FA Cup fourth round: Derby County's Max Bird on what losing his dad taught him about life and loss
entries.description: As Derby County prepare to face West Ham in the FA Cup, midfielder Max Bird explains how football has helped him deal with the loss of his dad.

entries.title: X Games: Britain's Zoe Atkin wins first gold in Ski Superpipe

entries.title: Artur Beterbiev v Anthony Yarde: Fight Talk - boxing world reacts to 'fight of the year contender'

entries.title: The Papers: 'Hospitals at home' plan and 'asylum hotel racism'

entries.title: Wales rugby chief executive Phillips set to leave role

entries.title: Gove says lax rules partly to blame for Grenfell fire

entries.title: New US childhood obesity guidelines criticised by families

entries.title: NHS: More at-home care offered in attempt to shorten waiting times

entries.title: Struggling coast areas 'at risk of being forgotten'

entries.title: Mensa: What happens when 'child geniuses' grow up

entries.title: Happy Valley's Ryan: Rhys Connah on starring in hit TV drama then and now

entries.title: Tyre Nichols: Police unit is disbanded after death

entries.title: 'Elon Musk has made me embarrassed to drive my Tesla now'
entries.description: Elon Musk was once hailed as the secret to Tesla's success. Now he's one of its problems.

entries.title: Television frontman Tom Verlaine dies at 73
entries.description: His band rose to fame in the 1970s New York punk scene, scoring UK hits including Marquee Moon.

entries.title: The joy and the trauma of carrying a celebrity's baby
